The diffusion rates of gases can be expressed by means of their number of moles diffusing through a porous medium during the same time. The total number of diffusing NH3 (nNH3) and Ar (nAr) moles is n = nNH3 + nAr, which we can substitute in Eq. (9) as10vNH3vAr=nNH3nAr=nNH3n-nNH3=MArMNH3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
